13 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND THE SENATE OF THE
14 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
15 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
16 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
17 the following proposed amendment to the Constitution of the State of
18 Oklahoma by adding a new Section 8 to Article VIIB thereof, to read
19 as follows:
20 Section 8. This act shall be known and may be cited as the
21 "Oklahoma Judicial Reform Act of 2025".
22 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
23 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
24 the following form:
Req. No. 12199 Page 1
1 BALLOT TITLE
2 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
3 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
4 This measure adds a new section to Article 7B of the Oklahoma
5 Constitution. It creates the Oklahoma Judicial Reform Act of
6 2025.
7 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
8 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
9 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
10 SECTION 3. The Chief Clerk of the House of Representatives,
11 immediately after the passage of this resolution, shall prepare and
12 file one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in
13 SECTION 2 hereof, with the Secretary of State and one copy with the
14 Attorney General.
